---
const objectives = [
    'To help one person operate with greater clarity, reach, judgment, and follow-through.',
    'To build tools and systems that make professional capability feel more personal, more powerful, and more alive.',
    'To create leverage without losing ownership.',
    'To make serious software that still feels playful to build and satisfying to use.',
];
---

<div class="essay-page manifesto-page">
    <section class="page-hero-simple manifesto-source">
        <p class="eyebrow">Foundations / Manifesto</p>
        <p class="manifesto-source__date">Rev May 20, 2026</p>
        <h1 class="page-display-title">access to agency</h1>
    </section>

    <section class="page-module manifesto-prose">
        <p>
            I wasn't alive when the Whole Earth Catalog was in print. I honestly
            had no idea what it even was until very recently and although I had
            likely heard the quote <em>Stay Hungry. Stay Foolish.</em>, it
            definitely wasn't a meaningful quote in my life. That has changed
            for me in a pretty radical way over the last few years. I went so
            far as to seek out the Whole Earth Epilog, an original copy of which
            now hangs framed in my office. I look at it most days, and it makes
            me happy every time I do.
        </p>

        <figure class="manifesto-figure page-module specimen-frame">
            <img
                src="/stay-hungry-stay-foolish.png"
                alt="Stay Hungry. Stay Foolish. image from Gilman's framed Whole Earth Epilog"
            />
            <figcaption>
                A touchstone from the Whole Earth Epilog that now hangs framed
                in my office.
            </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <p>
            That is what GalexC is to me. I was inspired by the incredible work
            Kyle Jensen was sharing with me through KyleOps, his personal AI.
            The level of clarity and depth across a complex, clearly evolving
            system was unlike anything I had ever seen before. Explaining
            complex DevOps concepts and setups is seriously challenging, and
            KyleOps cranked it out in a few minutes with an extremely cogent,
            actionable, helpful summary. Magic.
        </p>

        <p>
            As an homage to the Whole Earth Catalog, which had a simple yet
            expansive description
        </p>

        <blockquote class="manifesto-quote">
            <p>access to tools</p>
        </blockquote>

        <p>
            I would like to propose that GalexC exists to provide <em
                >access to agency</em
            >.
        </p>

        <p>
            I want to build something that allows people to act on <em>ideas</em
            > in their own way, for their own passions, and in a new way that is truly
            impossible without AI.
        </p>

        <p>
            For the sake of clarity, I explicitly do <strong>not</strong> want to
            join the race to build the next monolithic, SaaS-era, walled-garden software
            we've been made to accept. AI can be something truly incredible, if we
            build it.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="page-module manifesto-prose">
        <p class="eyebrow">Professional-Grade Personal AI</p>

        <p>On a practical level:</p>

        <blockquote class="manifesto-quote manifesto-quote-strong">
            <p>GalexC is Professional-Grade Personal AI</p>
        </blockquote>

        <div class="manifesto-objectives">
            <p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                {objectives.map((objective) => <li>{objective}</li>)}
            </ol>
        </div>

        <p>
            If GalexC achieves its objectives, it could make room for better
            work, better decisions, and a better way of moving through the
            digital world. If it never becomes more than what it is today, a
            personal project that has been genuinely, deeply fun to build, I
            count this as a success.
        </p>

        <p class="manifesto-closing">Personal first. Professional grade.</p>
    </section>
</div>
